  "description": "Åke Bertil Brovik was a Swedish artist known for his portrait paintings. He was born in 1911 in Gothenburg to V.E. Nilsson, a Police Commissioner, and Hulda Svenungsson. He married Birgit Wirde in 1939 and they had two children, Ingela and Bertil. He completed his studies at Valand Academy and the School of Arts and Crafts in Gothenburg. He traveled for studies in France, Switzerland, Norway, Denmark, Germany, and Czechoslovakia. He worked as a freelancer and was also a substitute drawing teacher at several places such as Vasa School and Gothenburg School of Arts and Crafts, and illustrated several books. In 1946, his works were exhibited at the Gothenburg Museum, and he completed a mural in the Schwedenhaus in Zurich in 1947. His hand-printed fabrics were displayed at several museums. His hobby was creating ex libris prints. He received several awards, including the Ordre Universel du Mérite Humain and was a honorary member of the Societas Sanctae Apolloniae." 
